Property.Name: Redox potential
Property.Description: One-electron redox potentials of phenols at pH 7

Property.Name: Logarithm of second-order rate constant
Property.Description: ks represents the second-order rate constant for the reaction of vitamin E derivative with stable substituted phenoxyl radicals (ArO•) [2,6-di-tert-butyl-4-(4-methoxy phenyl)phenoxyl] in ethanol at 25.0°C, using stopped-flow technique.

Property.Name: Trolox equivalent antioxidant capacity
Property.Description: TEAC is defined as the millimolar concentration of Trolox with the same antioxidant activity as a 1 mM concentration of the substance under investigation. Trolox - a water-soluble vitamin E analog
